name: What I Saw
description:
All we see are flowers,
Flowers that blooms from is sweetest till it's bitter,
A bud sprouted with naivety,
Eradicated by life's cruelty,
The sooner it blooms the sooner it wilts,
Like a butterfly in the wind not going with but against,
For how will a child learn from his ignorance,
When he's swaying in its trance,
Oh how foolish can you be my little child,
You're dancing in a trance but your time is running wild.
